original: Holmström, Tor-Hugo Fredrik, komminister. Ljungbyholm, f. 18/6/10 i Ljungby, Kalm. 1., av Tor H. o. Ruth Peters. G. 41 m. Margit f. Rehnefors. Barn: Inger o. Nils Fredrik ff. 43. — Stud:ex. i Kalm. 28, teol. fil. ex. i Lund 29, teol. kand., prakt. teol. prov o. prästv. f. Luleå stift 33. Tjg. s. e. o. prästman i Seskarö o. Överluleå, kontr:adj. i Haparanda, stiftsadj. i Övertorneå samt kyrkoadj. o. v. pastor i Traryd, kommin. i Ljungby sed. 42.
translated: Holmström, Tor-Hugo Fredrik, parish priest. Ljungbyholm, born on June 18th, 1910 in Ljungby, Kalmarnas. First child of Tor H. and Ruth Peters. Married in 1941 to Margit (nee Rehnefors). Children: Inger and Nils Fredrik born in 1943. Holmström passed his high school exam in Kalmarnas in 1928, theology and philosophy exam in Lund in 1929, received a theology degree as well as practical theology exam and was ordained as a priest for the diocese of Luleå in 1933. He served as a chaplain and priest in Seskarö and Överluleå, district vicar in Haparanda, diocesan vicar in Övertorneå, as well as a parish assistant and acting pastor in Traryd before becoming a parish priest in Ljungby in 1942.
